sp.p:
Vel shayd Daughter, dou dosht spake like an aable shaint, indeed gra;
but I must complain upon you for dis waanity, if dou musht have some waanity,
joy pridee now taake shome fitt days for dat occaasion of waanity.

Perhaps I might be in Love, if I shou'd see that gallant Cavallier osten;
but now I know not who he is, or whether ever I shall see him more▪ He is
the most Charming Man that ere was seen.

Go to, Mistriss you're too bold, very pious women may fall in Love;
this Man is Rich, Wife and Grave: My House and your Honour both need a
Man of Reputation to guard 'em.

Of Teives de housh breaktief, de shtreet tief dat do's Robb upon de Pockett,
de pad teife of de Road, and de horse teife, de Sodomite, and de Murderer;
just as day vere going to be hang'd. Nine and Fourscore.

Ahoo, I have losht dis braave occasion;
(She gets loose, and runs, he runs after her.
now phaat vill I do for anodder?

Ah me, that I should live to see this hour: I a Bawd! out on thee;
thou art a▪ Whore, and a silly one, to run up and down in this lewd manner▪
at these wicked hours; canst thou not be a Whore, and keep thy Reputation?

Millions of blessings fall on thee, my dear, dear Elvira, author of my life;
and liberty; haste, haste, lest my Aunt, or the Duoena, should surprise us. Farewel
my dear, dear Elvira.

I'le watch him coming out of his Father's house, and see how my Letter
works on the persidious man. Who's yonder? the old Lady with a Young Genman;
I suppose he is the brother or the Kinsman of her injur'd Neice.

I am as much a Cavalier as any man; my manifold atchievements witness
for me, the world rings of 'em; and one thing, sprig of honour, I tell thee,
no man in Madrid has more Castilian blood running in his Veins than I.

                  (to Elvira.) She tinks not dat I am after maaking Luscindo and you one;
and now I have revenged her contumely upon mee, in putting de out-side of de
door upon me. Daughter, phen dou dosht die, dou vilt be a gallant Saint indeed.
